window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>From the critically acclaimed author of </b><b><i>The 25th Hour </i></b><b>and </b><b><i>When the Nines Roll Over</i></b><b> and co-creator of the HBO series</b><b><i> Game of Thrones</i></b><b>, a captivating novel about war, courage, survival - and a remarkable friendship that ripples across a lifetime. </b></p> <p>During the Nazis’ brutal siege of Leningrad, Lev Beniov is arrested for looting and thrown into the same cell as a handsome deserter named Kolya. Instead of being executed, Lev and Kolya are given a shot at saving their own lives by complying with an outrageous directive: secure a dozen eggs for a powerful Soviet colonel to use in his daughter’s wedding cake. In a city cut off from all supplies and suffering unbelievable deprivation, Lev and Kolya embark on a hunt through the dire lawlessness of Leningrad and behind enemy lines to find the impossible. </p> <p>By turns insightful and funny, thrilling and terrifying, the<i> New York Times</i> best seller <i>City of Thieves </i>is a gripping, cinematic World War II adventure and an intimate coming-of-age story with an utterly contemporary feel for how boys become men.</p>"; 
